reviews.headline: Great product for the price point
reviews.comments:
In my search for a nice pinkish nude lip liner I came across the Morphe Soulmatte collection. I have never owned a Morphe product before so I was hesitant but given the price I decided that it was worth a try. I bought the lip mousse and liner in the color Wifey. The liner is a nice nude pink color that glides on smoothly and matches well with the mousse. The lip mousse is richly pigmented and after drying down it does stay put quite well, I didn't see any color transfer to my coffee cup after drinking. 

Overall this is a great product for the price and the color is very flattering. I will use the mousse on occasion but the liner will be a staple for me, it is perfection when paired with a sheer nude or pink balm! Wifey is the color I had been hoping for when I bought Charlotte Tilbury Pillow Talk (which is still a beautiful color but leans heavier toward pink than nude on me).

faceoff_positive.comments:
I was able to try Morphe Soulmate Hydrafill Gel Lipliner through Bizz Agent! I am so thankful for the opportunity because I had always been a little intimidated by lip liners. This product as been a game changer! I have a scar at the corner of my lip, so sometimes certain lip products enhance attention to the scar. However, with this lip liner I was able to basically disguise my scar! 

The gel liner glides smoothly! I am not sure if I am doing it right but I line my lips before I apply the lipstick/lipgloss. I am amazed at the difference between using lip liner with lipstick/lipgloss vs just using lipstick/lipgloss alone. 

The color soulmate was a perfect match for my skin tone! I have brown eyes, warm undertone skin color, and brown hair with face framing highlights. I use alot of natural eyeshadow, a peachy pink blush, and the soulmate color was the perfect shade for me. I used the gel lip liner with matte lip gloss when I had more of glam smokey eye look, and a natural soft eyeshadow. The Soulmate matte lip color looked perfect with any style of make up I did. 

I will definitely be using Morphe lipliner as part of my makeup routine now. 

Again, I am so thankfull to Bizz Agent for this opportunity. 

The package the Morphe lipliner came in added to the excitement, it was soo beautiful and thrilling to open! I can't wait to order more colors. 

The only thing I wish is that the color lasted all day. I notcied about 2 or 3 hours I either needed to touch up, or reapply.
faceoff_positive.headline: First time using lip liner SUCCESS!

faceoff_negative.comments: So I'm a fan of lip liners. I mean I don't apply gloss or lipstick with out it. I love the combo and how it compliments the gloss I just don't think the colors work well together for my skin type. Ima a darker liner lighter lip kinda girl! So I'm totally for the product and the brand and the formula used to make this liner. It glides on smoothly. Products payoff is simply wonderful. Just when it comes to preference I wouldn't get this color!
